Class PSItemComponent

java.lang.Object
  com.percussion.cms.objectstore.PSDbComponent
      com.percussion.cms.objectstore.PSItemComponent
All Implemented Interfaces:
IPSCmsComponent, IPSDbComponent, Cloneable
Direct Known Subclasses:
PSCoreItem, PSItemChild, PSItemChildEntry, PSItemField, PSItemFieldMeta, PSItemRelatedItem
public abstract class PSItemComponent
extends PSDbComponent

All IPSDbComponents associated with an item must derive from this class. It requires additional functionality that is unique to the way the item is processed.

Version:
1.0

loadXmlData

public abstract void loadXmlData(Element sourceNode)
                          throws com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSUnknownNodeTypeException
This method is called to populate an object from its XML representation. It assumes that the object may already have a complete data structure, therefore method only overlays the data onto the existing object. An element node may contain a hierarchical structure, including child objects. The element node can also be a child of another element node.

Parameters:
sourceNode - the XML element node from which to populate. Must not be null.
Throws:
com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSUnknownNodeTypeException - if the XML element node does not represent a type supported by this class.

toXmlCollection

protected static void toXmlCollection(Element el,
                                      Document doc,
                                      Collection col,
                                      com.percussion.cms.objectstore.PSAcceptElements accept)
This toXml's all objects in the collection and appends the element returned by the call to el. Collections are of type PSDbComponent, this simply iterates through the collection calling toXml.

Parameters:
el - - must not be null.
doc - - must not be null.
col - - must not be null, must contain objects of PSDbComponent
accept - - this applies to the elements for which there may be special rules to determine inclusion in the returned element. For example a PSItemField may or may not include field value depending on the context. Binaries may not automatically loaded into the field and may require an explicit load. However, binaries may be saved to the system with all other fields values. Therefore there needs to be a way to allow inclusion and exclusion of field values in XML and this parameters value is what can determine if the value will be loaded.
